description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen at the RCH for enthusiastic, motivated and customer focused individuals to join our telephony team. The role holders will be Switchboard Operators with day to day operational, ‘hands-on’ responsibility for answering and handling Hospital switchboard service calls. You need to be able to display experience and knowledge of a busy/intensive call answering function and have demonstrated strong interpersonal skills within a relatively small team structure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are two vacant positions:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1 x Full-time post working 37.5 hours per week 08:00 – 16:00 Monday to Friday*&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1 x Part-time post working an average of 16.875 hours per rolling 4 week period.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Week 1 = Wed / Thurs 2pm - 10pm; Week 2 = Wed / Thurs / Fri 6am - 2pm;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Week 3 = Tues / Wed 8am - 4pm, Sun 2pm - 10pm; Week 4 = Thurs 8am – 4pm*&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*flexible to accommodate the needs of the Service including bank holidays, infrequent early, late, night and week-end shifts as required&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;See Job Description for full details.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Phill Dodd - Switchboard Team Leader (07770 447 873)&lt;/p&gt;
